title: SFH on Vancomycin Resistant Enterococci
content_text:
p>
			Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary for 
			Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, after attending a public function 
			today (August 4): Reporter: (On vaccine against Vancomycin Resistant Enterococci) Secretary for Food and Health: I am very concerned about the issue 
			of Vancomycin Resistant Enterococci (VRE). In a hospital setting, if 
			we cannot put in place a very stringent infection control, there 
			will be chances for the spread of this antibiotic resistant

will be chances for the spread of this antibiotic resistant 
			bacterium, which is a threat to some patients who have a low immune 
			response mechanism. I have met representatives from the Hospital 
			Authority earlier this week and learnt about their proposed actions 
			to tackle the problem. I have also appealed to all senior management 
			in the public hospitals to take the matter very seriously. Even for 
			those hospitals or clusters which might not have been affected by 
			the VRE for the time being, I have also urged them to take stringent

the VRE for the time being, I have also urged them to take stringent 
			infection control measures to contain this particular matter. Reporter: (On preventive measures against VRE) Secretary for Food and Health: It is a very basic issue of complying 
			with the hand hygiene measures. In all hospitals, there should be a 
			bottle of alcohol rub for all healthcare workers as well as the 
			patients themselves beside the bed of every patient. Before and 
			after getting in contact with every patient, healthcare workers

after getting in contact with every patient, healthcare workers should apply the alcohol hand rub. Even for the patients, they should also do so before and after going to the toilet. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript.)
